sentences: Christine Lavin (born January 2, 1952) is a New York City-based singer-songwriter and promoter of contemporary folk music.
She was the original host of Sunday Breakfast on WFUV in New York City and a founding member of the Four Bitchin' Babes when they were formed in 1990.
